Package: SpThreshold
Type: Package
Title: Replication Threshold for Bayesian Multilevel Models of Areal Data
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-04-20
Authors@R: c(
    person("Shuqi", "Lin", email = "shuqi.lin@yale.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0009-4016-0029")),
    person("Joshua L.", "Warren", email = "joshua.warren@yale.edu",
           role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6274-6970")))
Description: Fits Bayesian multilevel models for repeatedly measured areal
    spatial data under the Leroux conditional autoregressive (CAR) prior and
    its nonspatial counterpart, and computes a closed-form replication
    threshold m* beyond which the two models yield effectively equivalent
    posterior inference for regression coefficients. Posterior sampling is
    implemented in C++ via RcppArmadillo for speed.
License: GPL-3
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.13)
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
Suggests: spdep
Encoding: UTF-8
